value.title: A Trump Fund-Raiser for Maya Wiley? Yes, but It’s Mary Trump
value.excerpt: Ms. Trump, the president’s niece, has written a tell-all book and opposed his re-election. Now she’s holding an online event for Ms. Wiley, who’s running for mayor of New York.

value.title: Trump hints at 2024 presidential run in remarks at White House party
value.excerpt: President Trump hinted that he may launch a 2024 campaign to return to the White House, as he continues to fight the 2020 election results and refuses to concede to President-elect Joe Biden.

value.title: The Latest: Biden gives dire virus warning for next 2 months
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden has issued a dire warning about the spread of the coronavirus over the next two months, predicting as many as 250,000 deaths

value.title: Trump is leaving Washington as he governed — chaotically
value.excerpt: First Read is your briefing from "Meet the Press" and the NBC Political Unit on the day's most important political stories and why they matter.

value.title: Biden admits Dems 'forgot' rural America, says he did 'something good for the country' by beating Trump
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden said Democrats "forgot" rural America in an interview with New York Times opinion columnist Thomas L. Friedman published Wednesday.

value.title: US Supreme Court asked to block Biden win in Pennsylvania

value.title: As Trump Rages, Voters in a Key County Move On: ‘I’m Not Sweating It’
value.excerpt: Pre-election tensions ran high in Bucks County, Pa. But Biden supporters there are increasingly comfortable tuning President Trump out and moving on, with an eye toward January.

value.title: While Cuban-Americans in Florida came out big for Trump, Cubans stuck in Mexico pinned their hopes on Biden
value.excerpt: "I will remain hoping for a change. I'm glad Trump is out for good, and no thanks to my family in Florida," a Cuban doctor in Mexico told Insider.

value.title: William Barr breaks with Trump's election fantasy
value.excerpt: Attorney General William Barr just dealt the most credible blow to Donald Trump's lies about a stolen election, precisely because he previously often came across more as the President's personal lawyer than a neutral arbiter of justice.

value.title: Trump, Biden camps inspect Nevada election office ahead of Thursday hearing on lawsuit
value.excerpt: Attorneys for the Trump 2020 Campaign and representatives of Joe Biden’s six Nevada Electoral College delegates inspected a vote-counting location in Carson City on Tuesday in connection with a voter fraud lawsuit filed by the Trump team.

value.title: Donald Trump suggests 2024 presidential bid: 'I'll see you in four years'
value.excerpt: President makes comments to Republicans at a White House reception, where video shows dozens of people crammed together without masks

value.title: Hispanic lawmakers urge Biden to pick Lujan Grisham for HHS
value.excerpt: Members of the Congressional Hispanic Caucus have sent a letter to President-elect Joe Biden's transition team lobbying for New Mexico Gov. Michelle Lujan Grisham to be nominated for the role of health and human services secretary.

value.title: Brad Parscale accuses 'D-level' 'talking heads' around Trump for forcing him out of 2020 campaign
value.excerpt: Former Trump 2020 campaign manager Brad Parscale has accused "D-level" "talking heads" in the president's orbit of starting a whisper campaign that forced him out earlier this year.

value.title: U.S. judiciary, shaped by Trump, thwarts his election challenges
value.excerpt: U.S. President Donald Trump's reshaping of the federal judiciary has done little to help him win lawsuits challenging the election outcome, with Trump appointees rebuffing him and the U.S. Supreme Court showing little interest in getting involved.

value.title: GOP senators find bodybags with anti-Trump notes on their front porches
value.excerpt: Several GOP Senators were bombarded with dozens of bodybags at their homes on Tuesday by angry protesters pushing for COVID-19 relief after months of gridlock over negotiations in Congress.

value.title: Trump associates, including Giuliani, are asking for pardons
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump's associates are making appeals to him in the hopes of obtaining pardons before he leaves office, a source familiar with the matter told CNN on Tuesday.

value.title: Jake Tapper to interview Joe Biden and Kamala Harris in first joint interview since winning election
value.excerpt: CNN's Jake Tapper will interview President-elect Joe Biden and Vice President-elect Kamala Harris on Thursday in their first joint interview since winning the election, the network announced Tuesday.

value.title: Mnuchin says Trump 'wants to make sure there is not a shutdown'
value.excerpt: Two of the top negotiators in Washington -- House Speaker Nancy Pelosi and Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin -- spoke Tuesday afternoon about funding the government, weeks after talks broke down for a new stimulus package to respond to the Covid-19 pandemic and its economic fallout.

value.title: Frontrunners for Kamala Harris Senate seat praised Fidel Castro
value.excerpt: Two frontrunners for Vice President-elect Kamala Harris' Senate seat have praised former Cuban dictator Fidel Castro.

value.title: Live politics updates: Biden on COVID stimulus: 'Help is on the way'
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden called on Congress to approve an economic stimulus plan. He also suggested that a package would be followed up.

value.title: Pence returns to Georgia on Friday; Obama stars in new Ossoff TV ad
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence will return to Georgia on Friday to hit the campaign trail in the state’s twin Jan. 5 Senate runoff elections, where the Republicans' Senate majority is at stake.

value.title: Kamala Harris Celebrates 50 Days Until Biden Is President; Sarah Cooper, Rosanna Arquette and Others Respond
value.excerpt: Vice President-elect Kamala Harris took to Twitter this morning to happily remind people they are only 50 days away from Joe Biden 's January 20th Presidential Inauguration. As she put it, "Only 50 days until we get to call @JoeBiden President of the United States.

value.title: Trump tells Georgia governor to 'do something,' as Kemp says interfering with election is illegal
value.excerpt: President Trump on Tuesday told Georgia Gov. Brian Kemp to "do something" to overrule state election officials, claiming he would find a "gold mine" of fraud, as the governor's office maintained that Georgia law "prohibits" him from "interfering in elections."

value.title: Some Taiwanese immigrants fear Biden will ‘Make China Great Again.’ Can he win them over?
value.excerpt: Among Southern Californians with roots in Taiwan, there is strong support for President Trump. Some are single-issue voters who value their homeland’s interests above domestic issues.
